==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amadavat
<hw>Am`a*da*vat"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Indian
name. From <ets>Ahmedabad</ets>, a city from which it was imported to
Europe.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The strawberry finch, a small
Indian song bird (<spn>Estrelda amandava</spn>), commonly caged and kept
for fighting. The female is olive brown; the male, in summer, mostly
crimson; -- called also <altname>red waxbill</altname>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>amaduvad</asp> and
<asp>avadavat</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amadou</ent>⟦br⟧
